---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const seo = {
  title: 'Privacy Policy | KM Wellness Center | El Paso, TX',
  description:
    'KM Wellness Center privacy policy: how we collect, use, and protect your personal and protected health information.',
};
---
<BaseLayout {...seo}>
  <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy', href: '/privacy-policy/' }]} />
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p>
    See also our downloadable documents: Privacy Policy and Informed Consent (link the PDFs from
    /Website-Backup/documents/ once uploaded).
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>Who We Are</h2>
    <p>Our website address is: https://kmwellnesscenter.com</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What Personal Data We Collect and Why</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Contact Forms.</strong> We collect information entered in our contact forms for customer
      service purposes, which may include your name, email address, phone number, and any other
      details you provide.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email Marketing and SMS.</strong> When you sign up for our newsletter or enter your
      email and/or phone number in our forms, you consent to receive email and SMS communications for
      marketing purposes. You can opt out at any time.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Analytics.</strong> Our website uses Google Analytics 4 to collect information about the
      use of our site to help us improve it. Google Analytics collects the IP address assigned to you
      on the date you visit, not your name or other identifying information.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Advertising.</strong> We use the Meta Pixel and Google Ads remarketing to measure and
      serve advertising. You can opt out via Google Ads Settings and the Network Advertising Initiative
      opt-out page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How We Protect Your Data</h2>
    <p>
      We implement security measures including secure servers, encrypted network communications,
      regular software updates, and malware protection. Staff are trained in data protection best
      practices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Your Rights &amp; Contact</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to access the personal data we hold about you and request corrections or
      erasure (subject to data we must keep for legal, administrative, or security purposes).
    </p>
    <p>
      For privacy questions or data requests, contact: privacy@monsterlinkmarketing.com ·
      (915) 229-6606 · 1601 N Mesa, 2nd Floor, El Paso, Texas, 79902 (Mon–Fri 9AM–6PM).
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>This page summarizes the web privacy policy. The full HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices
      (protected health information uses, disclosures, and patient rights) is captured verbatim in the
      project archive at /Website-Backup/documents/Privacy-Policies-KMC.md.</em>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
